Having heard that, Californians willingly (for the most part) went along with orders to shelter in place and to practice social distancing.
At the same time, 1.6 million Californians had filed for unemployment as of March 31.
Pushback against the orders has started up and down the state, and it’s not surprising that Surf City, USA, Huntington Beach, was the site of the first large protest on Friday.
It’s easy to dismiss the Huntington Beach protestors as crazy white supremacists endangering themselves and others in the middle of a pandemic.
